      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THE JANITOR NZ (6) returns from a successful NZ raid where he won the Cambridge Flying Mile before a midfield finish in The Race. Terrific in the Sydney carnival prior, winning his Miracle Mile qualifier before getting within a head of Leap Top Fame in the main event. Has a great strike rate at this circuit and distance and should be too good for these. ATTACHMENT (2) raced parked so wasn't disgraced when beaten 4.4m last week. Much better served by the lower draw having come from there to score three back, one of three wins within his last six outings. TIMS A TROOPER (1) raced parked but toughed out a win two back then finished only 2.2m away when off the back row last week. Draws to be competitive again. MANILA PLAYBOY (5) won from a similar barrier three back and has done well to place in both outings since, missing by a nose in the next attempt before he was held up and beaten 2m last week. DASHING (3) gets his best draw since scoring three back, one of four straight wins here.",
